===2020 census===
As of the 2020 census,<ref name="GR2">{{cite web |url=https://www.census.gov |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |accessdate=2008-01-31 |title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> there were 9,517 people, 2,941 housing units, and 2,829 families residing in the CDP, of which contains an average of 3.09 persons each. The population density was 6,778.49/sq mi (2,617.26/km<sup>2</sup>). The racial makeup was 73.8% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 71.3% [[Non-Hispanic Whites|Non-Hispanic White]], 0.6% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.0% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 14.6% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.0% [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], and 9.8% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 11.7% of the population. 14% were foreign-born citizens.

Within the population, 7.3% were below the age of 5, 21.1% were below the age of 18, and 16.9% were over the age of 65. 51.4% were female.

The median value of owner-occupied housing units was approximately $592,000. The median households income in the CDP was $155,670 and the [[per capita income]] was $57,079. About 4.8% of all citizens live below the [[Poverty threshold|poverty line]].

